I'd really rate this as a 1.5 star neighborhood joint. returned this weekend to see if anything changed.  the specials sounded good.  NEVER AGAIN!  my duck was completely INEDIBLE.  aside from looking like it was "butchered" with a spork, the fat was not rendered AT ALL, the skin was a FLOPPY mess and i was unable to cut through any of it!  i heard the chef curse when he saw the server taking my dish away.  to top it off, despite having also returned our appetizer, the owner, standing a few feet away, did not even come to our table to check in.  it just ain't what it used to be.   two things to note: the people responsible for the only good things about the night have been there for years -- the mussels (in curry sauce) and fries  and our server. I
